        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20880",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ignore the second patch, obviously I cannot delete wrong attachements. The patch #1 is the right one.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-17T10:48:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-17T10:48:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20884",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree, (if I remember) : delete() is the only method provided by Zend_Db_Table that doesn't escape automatically the parameters it is passed.\nThat seems nonsense, but perhaps there is a good reason ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-17T12:16:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-17T12:16:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20892",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well I can't see any, at least not in this implementation. When there are no additional paremeters given, any question mark in the $where clause is ignored, so it will all stay backward compatible.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-17T17:48:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-17T17:48:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20893",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jasoneisen",
                        "name": "jasoneisen",
                        "displayName": "Jason Eisenmenger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For the sake of uniformity I would suggest passing the second arg as an array.  IIRC $db->query() works this way.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jasoneisen",
                        "name": "jasoneisen",
                        "displayName": "Jason Eisenmenger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-17T18:44:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-17T18:44:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21093",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please evaluate and categorize as necessary.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-18T13:20:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-18T13:20:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21934",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=letssurf",
                        "name": "letssurf",
                        "displayName": "James Dempster",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It would certainly make using delete easier.\n\nI think it would be better to make it...\n{code}\n$myModel->delete('foo = ? AND bar = ?', array($foo, $bar));\n{code}\n\nJust in case we would ever want to add a third argument.\nAlso it make's it easy to pass a list of elements to bind.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=letssurf",
                        "name": "letssurf",
                        "displayName": "James Dempster",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-05-26T00:50:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-05-26T00:50:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23139",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "An update from my side, Zend_Db_Table::update() should also have that quoting functionallity.\nBy the way another nice thing would be, if you could also supply a Zend_Db_Select() for both update() and delete() method for more complex operations.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-28T10:00:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-28T10:00:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27821",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue has gone unaddressed for too long. I'm re-assigning to Ralph for re-evaluation and categorization.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-06T14:29:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-06T14:29:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33070",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=at465",
                        "name": "at465",
                        "displayName": "Andy Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I wouldn't recommend doing this as a variable number of arguments. It makes calling the function when you have an array of bind parameters much harder. See #ZF-3074 for an alternate way, just as James suggested, including patch and tests, along with Zend_Db_Table implementations as well.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=at465",
                        "name": "at465",
                        "displayName": "Andy Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-30T13:24:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-30T13:24:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41795",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just taking out the \"Fixed Version\".",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-30T06:51:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-30T06:51:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41798",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Why can't you use the where format that is expected (by Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract in update and delete):\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$model->delete(array('foo = ?' => $foo, 'bar = ?' => $bar));\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSeems like this is a non issue, if the issue is about automatic quoting.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-30T07:52:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-30T07:52:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41799",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jasoneisen",
                        "name": "jasoneisen",
                        "displayName": "Jason Eisenmenger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue has been tossed from one \"fix version\" to the next for 2.5 years.  Does this even still apply?  If so, I still hold firm on my previous comment.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jasoneisen",
                        "name": "jasoneisen",
                        "displayName": "Jason Eisenmenger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-30T07:59:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-30T07:59:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43136",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "linking related issue",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-19T06:09:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-19T06:09:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43137",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm closing this one, as we have discussed this a few times, and there is a solution to this problem available already, it simply is not the one suggested. As mentioned in ralphs previous comment, this notation will allow bindings for where clauses on update \/ delete calls.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$db->update('table', $data, array('foo  = ?' => $bar, 'baz = ?' => $bat));\r\n{code}\r\n{code}\r\n$db->delete('table', array('foo  = ?' => $bar, 'baz = ?' => $bat));\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThere is no point keeping this open for another 2 years!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-19T06:11:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-19T06:11:32.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
